{"word":"Περσίς","slug":"Περσίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Περσίς</b></el> <el>(Περσίς, ίδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:Περσικός'><el>Περσικός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>Persian</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, (.] (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>γῆ</el>), <i>Persis, Persia</i>, now <i>Farsistan</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>(<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>γυνή</el>), <i>a Persian woman</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>(<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>χλαῖνα</el>), <i>a Persian cloak</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}